HEADWORD: Cottoid
<hw>Cot"toid</hw> <pr>(k?t"toid)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>cottus</ets> sculpin + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Like a fish of the genus <gen>Cottus</gen>.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A fish belonging to, or resembling, the genus
<gen>Cottus</gen>. See <er>Sculpin</er>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

